quote: All are one
author: Heraclitus

quote: If you want to identify me, ask me not where I live, or what I like to eat, or how I comb my hair, but ask me what I am living for, in detail, ask me what I think is keeping me from living fully for the thing I want to live for.
author: Thomas Merton

quote: I see your picture and in that picture I didn't see you.
author: Santosh Kalwar,  Obscurity

quote: Who in the world am I? Ah, that's the great puzzle.
author: Lewis Carroll,  Alice in Wonderland

quote: I am a citizen of the world.
author: Diogenes of Sinope,  The Lives and Opinions of Eminent Philosophers

quote: Do you want to know who you are? Don't ask. Act! Action will delineate and define you.
author: Thomas Jefferson

quote: Who are you?"I asked."You know who I am,"he replied. "I'm yours."~Clea / Sage, pg. 105
author: Hilary Duff,  Elixir

quote: Who are you? No really. Way, way down deep. Who are you?
author: Doug Dillon

quote: If you want me again look for me under your boot soles.
author: Walt Whitman,  Leaves of Grass

quote: Tell me who admires and loves you, and I will tell you who you are.
author: Antoine de Saint-Exupery

quote: Do you wanna play? Everyone's dead, so I got bored. Did you come to play with me?--Wrath
author: Hiromu Arakawa

quote: I am my world.
author: Ludwig Wittgenstein

quote: God, who am I?
author: Sylvia Plath,  The Unabridged Journals of Sylvia Plath

quote: My ego is the wall between you and me.
author: Debasish Mridha

quote: I want a billion people to know my name as well as they know their own. I want to clone myself to fame.
author: Jarod Kintz,  I Want Two apply for a job at our country's largest funeral home, and then wear a suit and noose to the job interview.

quote: Don't think, but look! (PI 66)
author: Ludwig Wittgenstein

quote: Find what you want. I will find you.
author: Lloyd Alexander,  Westmark

quote: Do your actions define who you are, or does your purpose define why you are?
author: Debasish Mridha

quote: All I can be is me- whoever that is.
author: Bob Dylan

quote: Life is now in session. Are you present?
author: John C. Maxwell,  The 15 Invaluable Laws of Growth: Live Them and Reach Your Potential

quote: Whatever you are, be a good one.
author: Abraham Lincoln

quote: My identity was a big issue when I was a teenager, and I had a lot of questions, like: 'Who am I?' 'Who do I belong to?' But when I was still quite young, I decided that belonging is a tough process in life, and I'd better say I belonged to myself and the world rather than belonging to one nationality or another.
author: Hiam Abbass

quote: I still don't belong to anyone - I am mine.
author: Morrissey

quote: Look up.
author: Luanne Rice,  Silver Bells

quote: To solve a problem, change your awareness, perception, and consciousness about the problem.
author: Debasish Mridha

quote: You matter.
author: Suzanne Young,  The Treatment

quote: I belong, and my penis, it be long.
author: Jarod Kintz,  This Book is Not FOR SALE

quote: If you want me, you’d better hurry. Act now, supplies are limited.
author: Jarod Kintz,  This Book is Not FOR SALE

quote: I am a real person that cares about his art and cares about what he's doing - I have a heart and a soul and want to touch people and give.
author: LL Cool J

quote: I can't go on, I'll go on.
author: Samuel Beckett,  I Can't Go On, I'll Go On: A Samuel Beckett Reader

quote: I may not know you, but I don’t see any difference between you and me. I see myself in you; we are one.
author: Debasish Mridha

quote: I am unique...I play by a different set of rules; I am not intimidated by anything.
author: Jaachynma N.E. Agu

quote: I is for Integrity, be honest with yourself and others.
author: Lucas Remmerswaal,  The A-Z of 13 Habits: Inspired by Warren Buffett

quote: The square root of I is I.
author: Vladimir Nabokov,  Bend Sinister

quote: You climbed into my window in the middle of the night. So, either you're some kind of Vampire or some kind of Perv. Which is it?
author: Kami Garcia,  Beautiful Creatures

quote: Accept who you are. Unless you're a serial killer.
author: Ellen DeGeneres,  Seriously... I'm Kidding

quote: Even so, I’m somebody.I’m the Discoverer of Nature.I’m the Argonaut of true sensations.I bring a new Universe to the UniverseBecause I bring the Universe to itself.
author: Alberto Caeiro,  The Keeper of Sheep

quote: I’m going to follow this invisible red thread until I find myself again… until I finally figure out… who I’m meant to be.
author: Jennifer Elisabeth,  Born Ready: Unleash Your Inner Dream Girl

quote: Tell me whom you haunt and I’ll tell you who you are.
author: André Breton

quote: Life's most persistent and urgent question is, 'What are you doing for others?'
author: Martin Luther King, Jr.

quote: My wallpaper and I are fighting a duel to the death. One or the other of us has to go.
author: Oscar Wilde

quote: I’ve always hated the “Who are you?"question. This is a philosophical inquiry. Answering that question is why we’re on earth. You can’t answer it in thirty seconds or in an elevator.
author: Sandy Nathan,  Numenon

quote: I knew who I was this morning, but I've changed a few times since then.
author: Lewis Carroll,  Alice's Adventures in Wonderland & Through the Looking-Glass

quote: I have an idea of who I want to be, I have a vision of my own success.
author: Wiz Khalifa

quote: I had a dream about you. We were trying to come up with a hashtag to market our relationship. I suggested #fourlipsonekiss and #twomouthsonevoice, but you went with something confusing like #idontloveyou and #wearenotinarelationship.
author: Jarod Kintz,  We Had A #Dream About You

quote: Perhaps it's impossible to wear an identity without becoming what you pretend to be.
author: Orson Scott Card,  Ender's Game

quote: This is the city, and I am one of the citizens/Whatever interests the rest interests me
author: Walt Whitman

quote: Art doesn't interest me. Only artists interest me.
author: Marcel Duchamp

quote: I want to meet a guy named Art. I'd take him to a museum, hang him on the wall, criticize him, and leave.
author: Jarod Kintz,  I Want

quote: I don’t want fame, money, or duty. I want to close my eyes and see your loving beauty.
author: Debasish Mridha
